caller_intent: Nancy Barlowson wants to confirm that her insurance was properly transferred from her traded-in Veloster to her new 2022 Jeep Compass after a recent vehicle trade, and ensure there is no coverage lapse.
resolution_steps: Tracy confirms the new vehicle's details (2022 Jeep Compass, VIN 3D4NJDD1NT190036) and dealership (Foot Hill Ford).
Tracy notes Nancy hasn't transferred the tag yet and advises using a 30-day tag to avoid DMV issues.
Tracy proposes adjusting coverage: removing full coverage from the Jeep Compass (due to a loan) and keeping only liability coverage temporarily.
Tracy plans to contact Foot Hill Ford to obtain loan information for the Jeep Compass.
Tracy will update the Veloster policy to liability-only coverage until the tag is transferred.
knowledge_required: DMV requirements for temporary tags and coverage
Handling insurance policy adjustments for vehicle loans
summary: Nancy Barlowson contacted Alliance Insurance to confirm her insurance transfer after trading her Veloster for a 2022 Jeep Compass. Tracy identified a coverage gap and proposed temporary liability-only coverage for the Jeep Compass while verifying loan details with the dealership. The call concluded with Tracy committing to resolve the transfer and prevent DMV fines.
